{"nmem_brain_package": "1.0", "manifest": {"id": "3d6ca1f6-c880-42ea-a7aa-1fade1f3ab94", "name": "docker-essentials", "display_name": "Docker Essentials", "description": "Docker fundamentals and production practices: multi-stage builds, layer caching, security hardening, compose workflows, CI/CD integration, and the 12-factor methodology.", "version": "1.0.0", "author": "neural-memory", "license": "CC-BY-4.0", "tags": ["docker", "containers", "devops", "ci-cd", "deployment"], "category": "devops", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450930+00:00", "exported_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450930+00:00", "nmem_version": "4.33.0", "stats": {"neuron_count": 19, "synapse_count": 10, "fiber_count": 0}, "size_bytes": 12328, "size_tier": "micro", "content_hash": "sha256:2141d85629dd2b2f1d81edbb002fc4f1e6ee3352044f8e3876a26c3eeb9270b5", "scan_summary": {"risk_level": "clean", "finding_count": 0, "safe": true}, "rating_avg": 0.0, "rating_count": 0, "download_count": 0}, "snapshot": {"brain_id": "docker-essentials", "brain_name": "docker-essentials", "config": {}, "exported_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450725+00:00", "fibers": [], "metadata": {"quality": "curated", "source": "seed-generator"}, "neurons": [{"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Chose multi-stage builds over single-stage because they reduce final image size by 60-80%. Build dependencies stay in the builder stage, only runtime artifacts copy to the slim final image", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450642+00:00", "id": "dk-d1", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["docker", "optimization"], "type": "decision", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450642+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Chose Alpine-based images for production over Ubuntu because they're 5-10MB vs 70-100MB. Trade-off: musl libc can cause subtle compatibility issues with some Python packages (use python:slim as alternative)", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450651+00:00", "id": "dk-d2", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["docker", "images"], "type": "decision", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450651+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Chose docker compose for local dev over raw docker commands because it declaratively defines multi-service stacks (app + db + cache + worker) and provides consistent networking between containers", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450653+00:00", "id": "dk-d3", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["docker", "local-dev"], "type": "decision", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450653+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Each Dockerfile instruction creates a layer. Docker caches layers until a line changes — then invalidates ALL subsequent layers. Put rarely-changing instructions (apt install) before frequently-changing ones (COPY source code) to maximize cache hits", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450655+00:00", "id": "dk-i1", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["docker", "caching"], "type": "insight", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450655+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Running containers as root is a security risk. Always add `RUN adduser --disabled-password appuser` and `USER appuser` in your Dockerfile. If the app is compromised, the attacker has limited permissions", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450657+00:00", "id": "dk-i2", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["docker", "security"], "type": "insight", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450657+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Docker volumes persist data beyond container lifecycle. Named volumes (docker volume create) are managed by Docker. Bind mounts (-v /host:/container) map host directories. Use named volumes for databases, bind mounts for development hot-reload", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450658+00:00", "id": "dk-i3", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["docker", "storage"], "type": "insight", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450658+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Container health checks (`HEALTHCHECK CMD curl -f http://localhost:8000/health`) let Docker and orchestrators know when a container is truly ready, not just running. Critical for zero-downtime deployments", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450660+00:00", "id": "dk-i4", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["docker", "reliability"], "type": "insight", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450660+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": ".dockerignore is as important as .gitignore. Without it, `COPY . .` sends node_modules, .git, .env, and build artifacts to the daemon — slowing builds by minutes and leaking secrets into images", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450661+00:00", "id": "dk-i5", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["docker", "build"], "type": "insight", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450661+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Root cause: using `latest` tag in production means deploys are non-reproducible. A new push to latest changes what runs without any code change. Fix: always pin specific version tags or SHA digests", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450663+00:00", "id": "dk-e1", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["docker", "versioning"], "type": "error", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450663+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Root cause: COPY before dependency install invalidates cache on every code change. Fix: COPY requirements.txt first, RUN pip install, THEN COPY source. Dependencies cache survives code edits", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450664+00:00", "id": "dk-e2", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["docker", "caching"], "type": "error", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450664+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Root cause: containers sharing the default bridge network can reach each other by IP. Fix: create custom networks per stack (`docker network create myapp`), containers resolve by service name and are isolated from other stacks", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450666+00:00", "id": "dk-e3", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["docker", "networking"], "type": "error", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450666+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Docker image layers are read-only and shared. Running a container adds a thin writable layer on top (copy-on-write). This is why 10 containers from the same image use almost no extra disk", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450667+00:00", "id": "dk-f1", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["docker", "internals"], "type": "fact", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450667+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Compose file key directives: `build` (Dockerfile path), `image` (pre-built), `ports` (host:container), `volumes` (persistent storage), `environment` (env vars), `depends_on` (startup order), `healthcheck`, `restart: unless-stopped`", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450669+00:00", "id": "dk-f2", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["docker", "compose"], "type": "fact", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450669+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Docker resource limits prevent container from consuming all host resources. Set `--memory=512m --cpus=1.5` in run or `mem_limit` / `cpus` in compose. Without limits, one container can OOM-kill the host", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450670+00:00", "id": "dk-f3", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["docker", "resources"], "type": "fact", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450670+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Dockerfile best practices: 1) FROM specific-version 2) RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends 3) COPY deps first, install, then copy source 4) Multi-stage build 5) Non-root USER 6) HEALTHCHECK 7) LABEL for metadata", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450671+00:00", "id": "dk-w1", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["docker", "dockerfile"], "type": "workflow", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450671+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Container debugging: 1) `docker logs -f container` for stdout 2) `docker exec -it container sh` for shell access 3) `docker inspect container` for config/network 4) `docker stats` for CPU/memory 5) `docker compose logs --tail=100`", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450673+00:00", "id": "dk-w2", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["docker", "debugging"], "type": "workflow", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450673+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "CI/CD with Docker: 1) Build image in CI 2) Run tests inside container (consistent env) 3) Push to registry with git SHA tag 4) Deploy by updating image reference 5) Rollback = point to previous SHA", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450675+00:00", "id": "dk-w3", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["docker", "ci-cd"], "type": "workflow", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450675+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "Containers are process isolation, not VMs. They share the host kernel and use Linux namespaces (PID, network, mount) + cgroups (resource limits) for isolation. This is why containers start in milliseconds vs minutes for VMs", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450676+00:00", "id": "dk-c1", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["docker", "fundamentals"], "type": "concept", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450676+00:00"}, {"access_count": 1, "activation": 0.5, "brain_id": "seed", "content": "12-Factor App for containers: config via environment variables (not files baked into image), logs to stdout (not files), stateless processes (persist to external volumes/services), port binding via ENV, disposable (fast start/graceful stop)", "created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450678+00:00", "id": "dk-c2", "salience": 0.6, "state": "active", "tags": ["docker", "architecture"], "type": "concept", "updated_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450678+00:00"}], "synapses": [{"created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450690+00:00", "direction": "unidirectional", "id": "8a64193e-6e15-4245-8b22-f3ed3a1ccdda", "reinforced_count": 1, "source_id": "dk-d1", "target_id": "dk-i1", "type": "related_to", "weight": 0.9}, {"created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450694+00:00", "direction": "unidirectional", "id": "14392cde-6272-4520-9261-e35ed76a8af2", "reinforced_count": 1, "source_id": "dk-d2", "target_id": "dk-d1", "type": "related_to", "weight": 0.7}, {"created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450696+00:00", "direction": "unidirectional", "id": "985bc3bb-d9e7-4b21-bfb0-bd38e69eafcc", "reinforced_count": 1, "source_id": "dk-e2", "target_id": "dk-i1", "type": "caused_by", "weight": 0.9}, {"created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450699+00:00", "direction": "unidirectional", "id": "d131236f-0729-493d-9cee-5ec8e584e250", "reinforced_count": 1, "source_id": "dk-i2", "target_id": "dk-c1", "type": "related_to", "weight": 0.6}, {"created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450702+00:00", "direction": "unidirectional", "id": "9198aa88-e6e8-42cd-9271-a54fbf4a2554", "reinforced_count": 1, "source_id": "dk-e1", "target_id": "dk-w3", "type": "caused_by", "weight": 0.8}, {"created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450705+00:00", "direction": "unidirectional", "id": "8624767b-51fc-4761-925a-128c72e89480", "reinforced_count": 1, "source_id": "dk-i3", "target_id": "dk-c2", "type": "related_to", "weight": 0.7}, {"created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450707+00:00", "direction": "unidirectional", "id": "6b210acf-5bbf-4fbc-aa21-fb0c1fac7631", "reinforced_count": 1, "source_id": "dk-i5", "target_id": "dk-e2", "type": "related_to", "weight": 0.6}, {"created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450710+00:00", "direction": "unidirectional", "id": "300a34e4-9a2d-4f98-b68e-0724991bab41", "reinforced_count": 1, "source_id": "dk-f1", "target_id": "dk-c1", "type": "related_to", "weight": 0.9}, {"created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450712+00:00", "direction": "unidirectional", "id": "ca4fe45b-b213-44f2-8839-a2bc3938c758", "reinforced_count": 1, "source_id": "dk-w1", "target_id": "dk-d1", "type": "related_to", "weight": 0.8}, {"created_at": "2026-04-05T17:15:35.450714+00:00", "direction": "unidirectional", "id": "e19f1e7d-bba6-41f7-b3ab-488a99aef35b", "reinforced_count": 1, "source_id": "dk-i4", "target_id": "dk-f2", "type": "related_to", "weight": 0.5}], "version": "1"}}